164-166 Lewis Street, adjoining and at the S.E. corner of East 4th Street. No. 164 is a 3-story stable, and adjoins No. 166, which is directly at the corner.

June 10, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

172 to 176 Lewis Street (left), at, adjoining and north of the N.E. corner of East 4th Street. The corner house (No. 172), also bears No. 395 of the latter street. Also shown is east 4th Street, north side, east from and including Lewis Street to the East River.

June 10, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.
